  "supportCommunity": "<p>The following community resources are available to all JUHSD students and families. All services listed are free or low-cost unless otherwise noted.</p><h3>Emergency / Crisis Intervention</h3><table><thead><tr><th>Resource</th><th>Contact</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Emergency Services</strong> (ambulance, fire, police)</td><td>911</td></tr><tr><td><strong>211 Bay Area</strong> — free, confidential, 24/7, 150+ languages<br><a href=\"https://www.211bayarea.org\" target=\"_blank\">211bayarea.org</a></td><td>211</td></tr><tr><td><strong>StarVista Crisis Line</strong> — 24-hour support, free &amp; anonymous</td><td>(800) 273-TALK (8255)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Crisis Text Line</strong> — free 24/7 text support</td><td>Text HOME to 741741</td></tr><tr><td><strong>StarVista Youth Support</strong><br><a href=\"https://www.onyourmind.net\" target=\"_blank\">onyourmind.net</a> — talk live to trained peer mentors</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Youth Crisis Line</strong> (24/7)</td><td>(800) 843-5200</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Teen Line</strong> — trained teens answer calls 6–10 pm PST daily</td><td>(800) 852-8336</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Spanish Crisis Line</strong> (1–9 pm)</td><td>(800) 303-7432</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Counseling Services</h3><table><thead><tr><th>Resource</th><th>Contact</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Kara</strong> — grief support for adults, teens, and children<br>457 Kingsley Ave., Palo Alto<br><a href=\"https://www.kara-grief.org\" target=\"_blank\">kara-grief.org</a></td><td>(650) 321-5272</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Pyramid Alternatives</strong><br>480 Manor Plaza, Pacifica<br><a href=\"https://www.pyramidalternatives.org\" target=\"_blank\">pyramidalternatives.org</a></td><td>(650) 355-8787</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Rape Trauma Services (RTS)</strong> — counseling for survivors<br><a href=\"https://www.rapetraumaservices.org\" target=\"_blank\">rapetraumaservices.org</a></td><td>(650) 652-0598</td></tr><tr><td><strong>StarVista</strong> — crisis counseling &amp; community education<br>610 Elm St., Suite 212, San Carlos<br><a href=\"https://www.star-vista.org\" target=\"_blank\">star-vista.org</a></td><td>(650) 591-9623</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Pacifica Youth Service Bureau</strong> — youth &amp; family counseling<br>435 Edgemar Ave., Pacifica<br><a href=\"https://www.youthservicebureaus.org\" target=\"_blank\">youthservicebureaus.org</a></td><td>(650) 355-3900</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Child Abuse &amp; Relationship Safety</h3><table><thead><tr><th>Resource</th><th>Contact</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Childhelp National Child Abuse Hotline</strong> (24/7)</td><td>(800) 422-4453</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Community Overcoming Relationship Abuse (CORA)</strong></td><td>(800) 300-1080</td></tr><tr><td><strong>National Sexual Assault Hotline</strong></td><td>(800) 656-4673</td></tr><tr><td><strong>National Teen Dating Abuse Hotline</strong></td><td>(866) 331-9474</td></tr><tr><td><strong>RTS 24-Hour Crisis Line</strong></td><td>(650) 692-7273</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Love Is Respect</strong> — healthy relationship education<br><a href=\"https://www.loveisrespect.org\" target=\"_blank\">loveisrespect.org</a></td><td>(866) 331-9474 or text 22522</td></tr><tr><td><strong>One Love</strong> — healthy vs. unhealthy relationships<br><a href=\"https://www.joinonelove.org\" target=\"_blank\">joinonelove.org</a></td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Health Services</h3><table><thead><tr><th>Resource</th><th>Contact</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Daly City Youth Health Center</strong> — free health &amp; counseling (ages 12–24)<br>2780 Junipero Serra Blvd., Daly City<br><a href=\"https://www.dalycityyouth.org\" target=\"_blank\">dalycityyouth.org</a></td><td>(650) 985-7000</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Planned Parenthood — South San Francisco</strong></td><td>(877) 855-7526</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Planned Parenthood — San Mateo</strong></td><td>(650) 235-7940</td></tr><tr><td><strong>National Eating Disorder Hotline</strong><br>Mon–Thu 6am–6pm, Fri 6am–2pm PST</td><td>(800) 931-2237</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Alcohol, Tobacco &amp; Drug Abuse</h3><table><thead><tr><th>Resource</th><th>Contact</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Cannabis Decoded</strong> — youth cannabis education<br><a href=\"https://www.cannabisdecoded.org\" target=\"_blank\">cannabisdecoded.org</a></td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Alcohol and Drug Helpline</strong> (24/7)</td><td>(650) 573-3950</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Alcoholics Anonymous — San Mateo</strong><br><a href=\"https://www.aa-san-mateo.org\" target=\"_blank\">aa-san-mateo.org</a></td><td>(650) 577-1310</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Al-Anon / Alateen</strong> — support for family of drinkers<br>Spanish line available</td><td>(650) 873-2356</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Narcotics Anonymous — Peninsula</strong><br><a href=\"https://www.peninsulana.org\" target=\"_blank\">peninsulana.org</a></td><td>(650) 802-5950</td></tr><tr><td><strong>California Smokers' Helpline</strong></td><td>(800) 662-8887</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Food Services</h3><table><thead><tr><th>Resource</th><th>Contact</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>North Peninsula Food Pantry &amp; Dining Center</strong><br>31 Bepler St., Daly City — hot meals Mon/Tue/Thu 5–6 pm<br><a href=\"https://www.fooddc.org\" target=\"_blank\">fooddc.org</a></td><td>(650) 994-5150</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Housing &amp; Homelessness</h3><table><thead><tr><th>Resource</th><th>Contact</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Huckleberry House</strong> — 24-hour crisis shelter for youth<br><a href=\"https://www.huckleberryyouth.org\" target=\"_blank\">huckleberryyouth.org</a></td><td>(415) 621-2929</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Your House South (StarVista)</strong> — housing &amp; counseling for youth 10–17<br>394 Sequoia Ave., Redwood City</td><td>(650) 367-9687</td></tr><tr><td><strong>National Runaway Safeline</strong> (24/7, confidential)<br><a href=\"https://www.1800runaway.org\" target=\"_blank\">1800runaway.org</a></td><td>(800) 786-2929 or text 66008</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>LGBTQ+ Services</h3><table><thead><tr><th>Resource</th><th>Contact</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>GLBT National Help Center</strong> — peer support &amp; local resources<br><a href=\"https://www.glnh.org\" target=\"_blank\">glnh.org</a></td><td>(888) 843-4564</td></tr><tr><td><strong>LGBTQ Commission of San Mateo County</strong><br><a href=\"https://lgbtq.smcgov.org\" target=\"_blank\">lgbtq.smcgov.org</a></td><td>(650) 363-4872</td></tr><tr><td><strong>LYRIC — Center for LGBTQQ Youth</strong><br><a href=\"https://lyric.org\" target=\"_blank\">lyric.org</a></td><td>(415) 703-6150</td></tr></tbody></table>",
